metadata.name: Wabi-Sabi #1 - Tree of life
metadata.description:
Wabi-Sabi is a Japanese aesthetic originally derived from Buddhism. It is a world view, a feeling, an emotion, and is centered on the acceptance of transience and imperfection.

Sometimes all you need is just to look up to see.

Original Photograph by Oleg Sharov
Edition: 1/1
Size: 3600x2400 @ 240 dpi
